  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRACED ODE BURKINA FASO</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">bRACED will consolidate and scale up two tested methodologies (DFID/CA) for climate adaptation and building resilience, incorporating lessons and new partners and innovations. It found a major barrier to sustained change is the lack of access to appropriate and timely information and the space to challenge behavioural norms over time. By supporting the M&#xE9;t&#xE9;o Burkina and local media we will increase the quality and quantity of reliable, regular and user friendly climate information tailored for at-risk communities, particularly women and girls, and work with them to develop practical solutions for transformational change to build resilience to climate variability and disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x201C;Output 1. Community friendly climate information sharing and knowledge exchange mechanisms are established in 353 villages in Burkina Faso, to convey regular, reliable and understandable information about climate change, seasonal forecasting, early warning and practical solutions to build resilience&#x201D;. 
A1.1. Build and refine climate services in Burkina Faso in response to user needs
A1.2 Increase availability and quality of relevant information on weather and climate change at national level
A1.3 Increase availability and quality of relevant information on weather and climate change at local level

&#x201C;Output 2. Livelihoods of the most vulnerable people in 353 targeted villages in Burkina Faso, are improved with relevant and sustainable interventions to reduce their vulnerability to climate variability, extremes and disasters&#x201D;.
A2.1 Local Participatory Approach for risk management (at village level, linked to A3.1 process)
A2.2 Building local productive capacity through implementation of Soils and Water Conservation activities to  mitigate climate risk 
A2.3 Development, support and monitoring of IGA for the diversification of income sources 
A2.4 Multi-seasonal promotion of market garden production &amp; diet diversification</narrative>
  </description>
